g Burmese on their own will appreciate the accessible approach and the manageable size of the lessons of the very practical textbooks in this series.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aAsian Studies. 4aLanguage Arts & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Reference.2bisacsh1 aSwe, Daw Khin Mya.1 aTun, U Saw.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781609092214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781609092214/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK